00:21:39.726 --> 00:21:43.386
So Josh Debcher, computational scientist in CDS,

362
00:21:43.806 --> 00:21:47.726
built Chronos. Chronos models all these biases

363
00:21:47.766 --> 00:21:49.766
and noise to create a score,

364
00:21:51.766 --> 00:21:54.386
what we call the gene effect score, or Chronos gene effect score.

365
00:21:54.466 --> 00:21:58.126
So when you go to the portal, you are using the Chronos gene effect score.

366
00:21:58.546 --> 00:22:02.526
So this is the best score that we can give you that's closer

367
00:22:02.606 --> 00:22:05.926
to the truth of how sensitive a cell line when you

368
00:22:05.966 --> 00:22:09.826
suppress a gene, so that your discoveries can

369
00:22:09.866 --> 00:22:11.386
be validated.

370
00:22:13.426 --> 00:22:16.846
Now, finally, in this section, I'm going to talk about data

