460
00:27:48.290 --> 00:27:51.990
The ability to link molecular alterations to cancer

461
00:27:52.030 --> 00:27:55.910
vulnerabilities, because this, for the most part, is not possible just

462
00:27:55.950 --> 00:27:59.750
by sequencing genomes. But here now we have both the

463
00:27:59.760 --> 00:28:03.600
expression copy number, the baseline data, but we also have

464
00:28:04.190 --> 00:28:06.110
which genes are required for cell growth.

465
00:28:06.450 --> 00:28:10.190
So we can do link, in real time, those

466
00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:13.950
two data types and find biomarker-driven

467
00:28:14.010 --> 00:28:15.150
therapeutic targets.

468
00:28:16.470 --> 00:28:20.010
The community, all of you, there have been many

469
00:28:20.090 --> 00:28:23.970
discoveries and new interesting targets that are making their

470
00:28:24.030 --> 00:28:24.310
way,

471
00:28:25.310 --> 00:28:27.570
but today I'm going to highlight three of them.

472
00:28:28.190 --> 00:28:30.570
These are the ones that are closer to me, but also many

473
00:28:31.390 --> 00:28:35.200
are familiar to you, and particularly the first two, PRMT5 and

474
00:28:35.230 --> 00:28:37.290
Werners, maybe less so the third one.

475
00:28:38.610 --> 00:28:41.690
So one of the most common cancer

476
00:28:41.750 --> 00:28:44.790
alterations is the chromosomal arm deletion.

477
00:28:45.850 --> 00:28:49.710
These deletions, the cells want to delete the tumor suppressor gene, but there are

478
00:28:49.750 --> 00:28:52.350
many other genes that get co-deleted with it.

479
00:28:52.710 --> 00:28:56.310
Those genes might not be required for cell growth, but nevertheless, they can

480
00:28:56.330 --> 00:28:59.750
create vulnerabilities. So one of those is chromosome

481
00:28:59.970 --> 00:29:03.830
9p21. This is a locus that is very frequently deleted in cancer, one of

482
00:29:03.870 --> 00:29:06.890
the most frequently deleted. And

483
00:29:07.630 --> 00:29:11.500
with the tumor suppressor genes in this region, there are also other genes

484
00:29:12.030 --> 00:29:15.450
that are deleted, and in particular, this gene MTAP.

485
00:29:15.650 --> 00:29:19.290
MTAP is an enzyme that turns methylthioadenosine

486
00:29:19.350 --> 00:29:23.000
into methionine, and if the cells do not have MTAP, then they

487
00:29:23.010 --> 00:29:23.990
accumulate MTA.

488
00:29:25.230 --> 00:29:29.110
So a decade ago or so now, our teams wanted to

489
00:29:29.170 --> 00:29:33.070
identify if there were new dependencies created by

490
00:29:33.130 --> 00:29:36.650
MTAP deletion. So now we had the data to look for

491
00:29:36.730 --> 00:29:40.630
those. So we classified the cell lines into MTAP deleted or

492
00:29:40.730 --> 00:29:44.430
MTAP intact, and they look for dependencies using the shRNA

493
00:29:44.470 --> 00:29:47.550
data that were preferential in MTAP deleted.

494
00:29:49.950 --> 00:29:53.870
And we identified PRMT5. There were three manuscripts

495
00:29:54.730 --> 00:29:58.650
at the same time. They all converged into the same finding, that PRMT5

496
00:29:58.690 --> 00:30:02.090
was a selected dependency in MTAP-deleted

497
00:30:02.190 --> 00:30:06.170
cancers. And this is a very interesting

498
00:30:07.190 --> 00:30:09.070
biology story behind it, but I'm going to

499
00:30:10.310 --> 00:30:12.350
let you read the papers if you're interested.

500
00:30:13.170 --> 00:30:16.870
But I'll say that inhibitors of PRMT5 had reached

501
00:30:16.950 --> 00:30:19.430
clinical trials, so this is very exciting to us.

502
00:30:21.770 --> 00:30:25.350
Now, another very common genetic alteration in cancer is chromosomal

503
00:30:25.370 --> 00:30:28.970
instability. Microsatellite instability is one of

504
00:30:29.050 --> 00:30:29.430
such

505
00:30:30.410 --> 00:30:33.990
instabilities. This is caused by mismatch repair

506
00:30:34.030 --> 00:30:37.174
deficiencyAnd due to that,

507
00:30:38.274 --> 00:30:41.914
DNA replication errors that make the cells accumulate indels.

508
00:30:42.374 --> 00:30:46.074
So we hypothesized that this indel accumulation might lead to new

509
00:30:46.154 --> 00:30:49.034
vulnerabilities. So we took the same approach.

510
00:30:49.414 --> 00:30:53.334
We classified the cell lines into microsatellite stable and unstable,

511
00:30:53.774 --> 00:30:57.714
and now we have both CRISPR and our RNAi data,

512
00:30:58.254 --> 00:31:01.704
so we evaluated this in both, look for preferential

513
00:31:01.754 --> 00:31:04.294
dependencies in microsatellite unstable cell lines.

514
00:31:04.994 --> 00:31:08.914
And here we find the same both with CRISPR and shRNA.

515
00:31:08.994 --> 00:31:10.134
We had similar results.

516
00:31:10.994 --> 00:31:14.234
We found that Werner, which is a DNA helicase,

517
00:31:14.614 --> 00:31:15.014
was

518
00:31:16.314 --> 00:31:20.174
only sensitive, in this case, in MSI

519
00:31:20.614 --> 00:31:23.874
cell lines. In this case, there were also three manuscripts

520
00:31:24.534 --> 00:31:27.054
that were published together. So that's instant

521
00:31:27.974 --> 00:31:31.594
validation of this finding. So there were many

522
00:31:31.674 --> 00:31:35.514
companies that were going to develop inhibitors, and now they have reached

523
00:31:35.574 --> 00:31:38.014
clinical trials or they are being evaluated.

524
00:31:39.214 --> 00:31:42.934
In my third and last example, so after

525
00:31:43.054 --> 00:31:46.254
we had more CRISPR data, so when we did the

526
00:31:47.314 --> 00:31:49.654
MMTAP analysis, we only had shRNA data.

527
00:31:49.714 --> 00:31:52.854
Now we had a lot more CRISPR data, a lot more cell lines.

528
00:31:52.934 --> 00:31:56.114
So we revisited the 9p21 deletion,

529
00:31:56.774 --> 00:32:00.474
and we did the same analysis here. We classified the cell lines by

530
00:32:00.794 --> 00:32:04.494
9p deletion or intact, and again, look for dependencies.

531
00:32:04.944 --> 00:32:07.454
And reassuringly, we did find BRMT5,

532
00:32:08.334 --> 00:32:12.214
but we also find this other gene, Pelo, together with HBS1L,

533
00:32:12.334 --> 00:32:13.654
which form a complex.

534
00:32:15.054 --> 00:32:18.924
And then again, here now we had two publications coming

535
00:32:19.034 --> 00:32:22.964
out at the same time, and again, instant sort of validation of

536
00:32:22.994 --> 00:32:23.474
the finding.

537
00:32:24.594 --> 00:32:27.914
This one was particularly interesting because not only

538
00:32:28.074 --> 00:32:31.734
chromosome 1921 deletion, but we saw that some cell

539
00:32:31.794 --> 00:32:34.534
lines were still sensitive. They did not have the deletion.

540
00:32:35.004 --> 00:32:38.914
So we investigated that, and we found that microsatellite instability

541
00:32:38.994 --> 00:32:42.714
was also leading to Pelo dependency, which at first does

542
00:32:42.794 --> 00:32:46.553
seem a little bit strange. We also thought that we didn't know

543
00:32:46.594 --> 00:32:50.444
how this was all connected. It's a very interesting

544
00:32:50.534 --> 00:32:54.314
story if you want to read in the paper, but I'm just going to use this slide

545
00:32:54.334 --> 00:32:54.694
to

546
00:32:55.934 --> 00:32:59.414
connect them. So we found that focal deletion

547
00:32:59.894 --> 00:33:01.734
in chromosome 9p21

548
00:33:03.374 --> 00:33:07.094
was leading to the instability of this SKI

549
00:33:07.174 --> 00:33:09.234
complex. It's called super killer complex.

550
00:33:10.194 --> 00:33:13.334
And microsatellite instability was causing mutations in

551
00:33:13.354 --> 00:33:17.334
TTC37, and TTC37 was also part

552
00:33:17.374 --> 00:33:21.003
of this SKI complex, and mutations would cause this complex to

553
00:33:21.074 --> 00:33:24.534
be not functional and degraded.

554
00:33:25.294 --> 00:33:28.894
And then the SKI complex and Pelo as well, HBS1L, they both work to

555
00:33:28.934 --> 00:33:32.794
release ribosomes during translation when those

556
00:33:32.834 --> 00:33:35.994
get stuck during no go, no stop

557
00:33:37.234 --> 00:33:40.934
issues. So if you don't have SKI

558
00:33:41.634 --> 00:33:45.114
complex functional, now inhibit Pelo, the cells get pushed

559
00:33:45.154 --> 00:33:46.574
further, and they die.

560
00:33:50.114 --> 00:33:53.574
But beyond all these discoveries and specific

561
00:33:53.634 --> 00:33:57.234
examples, and these are the ones that are closer to me, but there are many

562
00:33:57.334 --> 00:34:00.934
others, interesting ones in the literature using DEMAP

563
00:34:01.014 --> 00:34:02.694
data. But beyond that,

564
00:34:03.534 --> 00:34:07.434
I think what we're really proud of is how DEMAP

565
00:34:07.514 --> 00:34:11.495
has democratized discovery. So with the DEMAP

566
00:34:11.554 --> 00:34:15.475
portal, we have more than 11,000 users per week, and we

567
00:34:15.515 --> 00:34:17.774
have visits from around the country.

568
00:34:18.314 --> 00:34:19.214
And so

569
00:34:21.334 --> 00:34:25.174
releasing this data into the portal has allowed labs, whether

570
00:34:25.194 --> 00:34:25.834
they have

571
00:34:26.894 --> 00:34:30.854
funding or they are more restricted,

572
00:34:31.254 --> 00:34:34.915
and whether they have computational expertise or not, to be

573
00:34:34.935 --> 00:34:38.435
enabled to use the data to make their discoveries.

574
00:34:38.554 --> 00:34:39.015
And

575
00:34:39.935 --> 00:34:43.814
since 2018, as I mentioned, we do scheduled releases.

576
00:34:43.874 --> 00:34:47.154
We had done 26 so far, and these releases

