00:36:47.342 --> 00:36:51.202
hundreds of models, including organoids, rare cancers, pediatric

610
00:36:51.262 --> 00:36:54.062
cancers, and neurospheres, and others.

611
00:36:55.542 --> 00:36:59.042
So we then wanted to integrate this data into

612
00:36:59.542 --> 00:37:00.622
our existing data,

613
00:37:01.942 --> 00:37:05.522
and we had to develop methods. So James Swander

