00:37:21.202 --> 00:37:24.982
set of more than 150 models. And importantly, we were

619
00:37:25.062 --> 00:37:28.582
able to incorporate that data together with all our

620
00:37:28.642 --> 00:37:32.202
existing data so that they can be explored in the portal.

621
00:37:33.462 --> 00:37:37.452
So soon, you will go to the portal, and you will be able to see dependencies,

622
00:37:37.602 --> 00:37:41.222
both in organoids and cell lines. Say, for the

623
00:37:41.262 --> 00:37:43.922
majority of dependencies, they do not change.

624
00:37:43.942 --> 00:37:47.472
We see the value of the organoids and the neurospheres.

625
00:37:47.522 --> 00:37:51.042
These new generation models help us expand the

626
00:37:51.102 --> 00:37:55.002
genomics and the transcriptional states that were not

627
00:37:55.042 --> 00:37:58.922
represented in Demap before. That being said, there

628
00:37:58.942 --> 00:38:00.462
are some interesting differences.

629
00:38:01.322 --> 00:38:04.582
For instance, the one I'm showing here is two integrins,

